To start with we need a few things needed for our application like Model View Controller(MVC) or MVVM patterns which is an architectural pattern used primarily by Apple's UIKit, Foundation etc. 
Model - This represents the data structure that serves as your business logic and will be manipulated in response to user actions (like tapping a button). Data access layer can also provide methods for retrieving/storing this model state from persistent storage like CoreData or Swift Preferences . It's basically responsible only with fetching, storing & deleting the data.
View - This is what your users see and interacts directly to manipulate user interface elements in response of a particular event (like tapping on button).  The view will display output for each state change that it observes within its model or any observer changes made by this object’s associated models, ie. updates/renders the UI as needed according with your application's needs and requirements
Controller - This is an intermediary between Model & View components which performs a specific action in response to user events (like tapping on button).  It will update model when necessary so that view reflects changes made by controller, ie. observes the actions performed above or below its own responsibility within your app’s business logic and should not know about data storage details
